A TV ad featuring the upcoming Samsung Galaxy S10 has been played on a Norwegian TV channel, offering an in-depth look at Samsung’s latest flagship device. The ad, which was posted on YouTube by a viewer, confirms various rumoured features. These include a fingerprint reader built into an Infinity-O display, a triple-lens rear camera design, and reverse wireless charging. The upcoming Galaxy Buds are also featured in the article, and are shown being charged by the Galaxy S10’s reverse charging functionality. Samsung is expected to launch three versions of the smartphone at tomorrow’s launch event – the S10e, S10, and S10+. The most powerful version of the S10+ is expected to pack 12GB RAM and 1TB storage, and will reportedly cost more than the top iPhone Xs Max. Watch the Samsung Galaxy S10 ad below. 